SELECT 'Episode 3: Melunakkan Besi dan Membuat Baju Besi', 'kisah-dawud-03-melunakkan-besi-dan-baju-besi', 'id', 'kisah-dawud', 3, 1, 'Karunia Allah kepada Dawud juga berupa keterampilan yang bermanfaat bagi umat manusia: kemampuan mengolah besi. Allah melunakkan besi di tangannya dan mengajarinya membuat baju perang. Allah berfirman, "Dan Kami ajarkan (pula) kepada Dawud cara membuat baju besi untukmu, guna melindungi kamu dalam peperanganmu. Apakah kamu bersyukur (kepada Allah)?" (QS. Al-Anbiya: 80).

Dalam Surah Saba'' dijelaskan bagaimana Allah membimbing cara pembuatannya secara rapi dan presisi, "…dan Kami telah melunakkan besi untuknya, (yaitu) buatlah baju besi yang besar-besar dan ukurlah anyamannya; dan kerjakanlah kebajikan. Sungguh, Aku Maha Melihat apa yang kamu kerjakan" (QS. Saba'': 10-11).

Yang menarik, Dawud adalah seorang raja yang tetap bekerja dengan tangannya sendiri. Ia tidak menggantungkan hidupnya pada kekayaan kerajaan, melainkan makan dari hasil kerjanya membuat baju besi. Ini menjadi teladan tentang kemuliaan bekerja dan mencari nafkah yang halal, betapapun tinggi kedudukan seseorang.

Hikmah: ilmu dan keterampilan adalah karunia yang harus disyukuri dengan cara memanfaatkannya untuk kebaikan. Dawud menyatukan tiga hal: kenabian, kerajaan, dan tangan yang bekerja — bukti bahwa ketakwaan tidak bertentangan dengan kerja keras.

Sumber & Catatan: dalil dari Al-Qur''an — QS. Al-Anbiya: 80 dan Saba'': 10-11. Keterangan bahwa Dawud makan dari hasil tangannya sendiri bersumber dari hadits sahih riwayat Bukhari (no. 2072), "Tidaklah seseorang makan makanan yang lebih baik daripada hasil kerja tangannya sendiri. Sungguh Nabi Dawud makan dari hasil kerja tangannya."', 0, 'qc_pending', 'ai_original', 'published', 1.0,
  (SELECT id FROM ayah WHERE surah_id = 21 AND number = 80), NULL, datetime('now');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO stories (title, slug, lang, series_key, episode_number, category_id, body, ai_generated, qc_status, source_format, status, confidence_score, related_ayah_id, pdf_ebook_id, published_at)
SELECT 'Episode 3: Softening Iron and Making Coats of Mail', 'kisah-dawud-03-melunakkan-besi-dan-baju-besi', 'en', 'kisah-dawud', 3, 1, 'Allah''s favor to Dawud also took the form of a skill of benefit to humankind: the working of iron. Allah made iron pliable in his hands and taught him to fashion armor. Allah said, "And We taught him the fashioning of coats of armor to protect you from your [enemy in] battle. So will you then be grateful?" (Qur''an 21:80).

Surah Saba'' explains how Allah guided the making of it with order and precision: "…and We made pliable for him iron, [commanding], ''Make full coats of mail and calculate [precisely] the links, and work righteousness. Indeed I, of what you do, am Seeing''" (Qur''an 34:10-11).

Remarkably, Dawud was a king who still worked with his own hands. He did not live off the wealth of the kingdom but ate from what he earned making armor. This is a model of the dignity of work and of seeking a lawful livelihood, however high one''s rank.

Reflection: knowledge and skill are favors to be thanked by using them for good. Dawud combined three things: prophethood, kingship, and a working hand — proof that piety does not clash with honest labor.

Source & Note: evidence from the Qur''an — 21:80 and 34:10-11. That Dawud ate from the work of his own hands comes from an authentic hadith reported by al-Bukhari (no. 2072): "No one has ever eaten food better than what he eats from the work of his own hand; and indeed the Prophet of Allah Dawud used to eat from the work of his hand."', 0, 'qc_pending', 'ai_original', 'published', 1.0,
  (SELECT id FROM ayah WHERE surah_id = 21 AND number = 80), NULL, datetime('now');

INSERT OR IGNORE INTO stories (title, slug, lang, series_key, episode_number, category_id, body, ai_generated, qc_status, source_format, status, confidence_score, related_ayah_id, pdf_ebook_id, published_at)
SELECT 'Episode 4: Hakim yang Adil dan Ujian di Mihrab', 'kisah-dawud-04-hakim-yang-adil-dan-ujian-mihrab', 'id', 'kisah-dawud', 4, 1, 'Allah menguatkan kerajaan Dawud dan memberinya kemampuan memutuskan perkara dengan tepat. Allah berfirman, "Dan Kami kuatkan kerajaannya dan Kami berikan kepadanya hikmah dan kebijaksanaan dalam memutuskan perkara (fashlal-khithab)" (QS. Sad: 20). "Fashlal-khithab" berarti ketegasan dan kejelasan dalam menimbang serta memutus suatu urusan — modal utama seorang hakim.

Al-Qur''an lalu mengisahkan sebuah ujian: dua orang yang berperkara memanjat dinding mihrab tempat Dawud beribadah. Salah satunya berkata bahwa saudaranya memiliki sembilan puluh sembilan ekor kambing betina, sedang ia hanya punya satu, namun saudaranya itu memintanya pula. Dawud pun segera menyimpulkan bahwa yang menuntut telah berbuat zalim (QS. Sad: 21-24).

Setelah itu Dawud menyadari bahwa peristiwa itu adalah ujian dari Allah atas dirinya. Ia pun bersegera memohon ampun dan bertobat. Allah berfirman, "…dan Dawud menduga bahwa Kami mengujinya; maka dia memohon ampunan kepada Tuhannya lalu menyungkur sujud dan bertobat. Lalu Kami mengampuni (kesalahan)nya itu. Dan sungguh, dia mempunyai kedudukan yang dekat di sisi Kami dan tempat kembali yang baik" (QS. Sad: 24-25).

Hikmah: seorang hakim harus mendengar kedua pihak sebelum memutus, dan sebesar apa pun kedudukan seseorang, ia tetap hamba yang bisa diuji dan perlu bertobat. Kebesaran Dawud justru tampak pada kesegerannya kembali kepada Allah.

Sumber & Catatan: dalil dari Al-Qur''an — QS. Sad: 20-25. Perlu dijujurkan: sebagian mufasir menyertakan cerita rinci berlatar Isra''iliyyat tentang sebab ujian ini, namun banyak ulama menolaknya karena tidak layak bagi kedudukan seorang nabi dan tidak ada dalam Al-Qur''an maupun Sunnah sahih. Maka kami cukupkan pada teks ayat: adanya ujian, lalu istighfar, sujud, dan tobat Dawud — tanpa menambah rincian yang tak terverifikasi.', 0, 'qc_pending', 'ai_original', 'published', 1.0,
  (SELECT id FROM ayah WHERE surah_id = 38 AND number = 20), NULL, datetime('now');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO stories (title, slug, lang, series_key, episode_number, category_id, body, ai_generated, qc_status, source_format, status, confidence_score, related_ayah_id, pdf_ebook_id, published_at)
SELECT 'Episode 4: The Just Judge and the Test in the Prayer Chamber', 'kisah-dawud-04-hakim-yang-adil-dan-ujian-mihrab', 'en', 'kisah-dawud', 4, 1, 'Allah strengthened Dawud''s kingdom and gave him the ability to decide matters rightly. Allah said, "And We strengthened his kingdom and gave him wisdom and decisive speech (fasl al-khitab)" (Qur''an 38:20). "Fasl al-khitab" means firmness and clarity in weighing and deciding an affair — the chief asset of a judge.

The Qur''an then relates a test: two litigants climbed the wall of the prayer chamber where Dawud was worshipping. One said his brother had ninety-nine ewes while he had only one, yet the brother demanded that one too. Dawud quickly concluded that the claimant had wronged him (Qur''an 38:21-24).

Afterward Dawud realized the event was a test from Allah for himself. He hastened to seek forgiveness and repent. Allah said, "…And Dawud became certain that We had tried him, and he asked forgiveness of his Lord and fell down bowing [in prostration] and turned in repentance. So We forgave him that; and indeed, for him is nearness to Us and a good place of return" (Qur''an 38:24-25).

Reflection: a judge must hear both sides before ruling, and however high one''s rank, he remains a servant who can be tested and needs to repent. Dawud''s greatness shows precisely in how quickly he returned to Allah.

Source & Note: evidence from the Qur''an — 38:20-25. In honesty: some commentators attach a detailed Isra''iliyyat backstory to this test, but many scholars reject it as unbefitting a prophet''s rank and absent from the Qur''an and authentic Sunnah. So we keep to the text of the ayat: a test, then Dawud''s seeking forgiveness, prostration, and repentance — without adding unverified detail.', 0, 'qc_pending', 'ai_original', 'published', 1.0,
  (SELECT id FROM ayah WHERE surah_id = 38 AND number = 20), NULL, datetime('now');

