SELECT 'Episode 5: Perkara Ladang dan Kearifan Dua Nabi', 'kisah-dawud-05-perkara-ladang', 'id', 'kisah-dawud', 5, 1, 'Al-Qur''an mengabadikan sebuah peristiwa peradilan yang melibatkan Dawud bersama putranya, Sulaiman. Allah berfirman, "Dan (ingatlah kisah) Dawud dan Sulaiman, ketika keduanya memberikan keputusan mengenai ladang, karena (ladang itu) dirusak oleh kambing-kambing milik kaumnya. Dan Kami menyaksikan keputusan (yang diberikan) oleh mereka itu" (QS. Al-Anbiya: 78).

Kambing-kambing suatu kaum masuk ke ladang orang lain pada malam hari dan merusak tanamannya. Keduanya memberi keputusan, lalu Allah memberikan pemahaman yang lebih tepat kepada Sulaiman. Namun Allah tidak mencela Dawud, bahkan memuji keduanya, "Maka Kami memberikan pengertian kepada Sulaiman (tentang hukum yang lebih tepat); dan kepada masing-masing Kami berikan hikmah dan ilmu…" (QS. Al-Anbiya: 79).

Yang indah dari ayat ini: dua nabi berbeda dalam sebuah keputusan ijtihad, namun keduanya tetap dipuji Allah sebagai pemilik "hikmah dan ilmu". Ini menjadi dasar bahwa perbedaan pendapat dalam ijtihad yang tulus tidak mengurangi kemuliaan, selama sama-sama mencari kebenaran.

Hikmah: kearifan sejati adalah mencari keputusan yang paling adil dan bermanfaat, serta lapang dada menerima bahwa orang lain bisa lebih tepat. Ilmu adalah karunia Allah yang Dia bagikan menurut kehendak-Nya.

Sumber & Catatan: dalil dari Al-Qur''an — QS. Al-Anbiya: 78-79. Al-Qur''an tidak merinci bentuk kedua keputusan itu; rincian yang beredar di kitab tafsir bersumber dari riwayat dan bukan bagian dari nas, sehingga kami cukupkan pada makna yang tegas dari ayat: keduanya berhikmah, dan Sulaiman diberi pemahaman yang lebih tepat pada kasus itu.', 0, 'qc_pending', 'ai_original', 'published', 1.0,
  (SELECT id FROM ayah WHERE surah_id = 21 AND number = 78), NULL, datetime('now');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO stories (title, slug, lang, series_key, episode_number, category_id, body, ai_generated, qc_status, source_format, status, confidence_score, related_ayah_id, pdf_ebook_id, published_at)
SELECT 'Episode 5: The Case of the Field and the Wisdom of Two Prophets', 'kisah-dawud-05-perkara-ladang', 'en', 'kisah-dawud', 5, 1, 'The Qur''an immortalizes a case of judgment involving Dawud together with his son Sulaiman. Allah said, "And [mention] David and Solomon, when they judged concerning the field — when the sheep of a people overran it [at night], and We were witness to their judgment" (Qur''an 21:78).

A people''s sheep had strayed into another''s field at night and ruined its crop. The two gave a ruling, and Allah gave Sulaiman a more precise understanding. Yet Allah did not blame Dawud; rather He praised them both: "And We gave understanding of it to Solomon, and to each [of them] We gave judgment and knowledge…" (Qur''an 21:79).

The beauty of this verse: two prophets differed in a matter of considered judgment (ijtihad), yet both remained praised by Allah as possessors of "judgment and knowledge." This is a basis that sincere difference in ijtihad does not diminish one''s honor, so long as both seek the truth.

Reflection: true wisdom is to seek the most just and beneficial ruling, and to be open-hearted in accepting that another may be more correct. Knowledge is a favor of Allah, which He apportions as He wills.

Source & Note: evidence from the Qur''an — 21:78-79. The Qur''an does not detail the form of the two rulings; the details circulating in tafsir come from reports and are not part of the text, so we keep to the plain meaning of the ayat: both had wisdom, and Sulaiman was given a more precise understanding in that case.', 0, 'qc_pending', 'ai_original', 'published', 1.0,
  (SELECT id FROM ayah WHERE surah_id = 21 AND number = 78), NULL, datetime('now');

INSERT OR IGNORE INTO stories (title, slug, lang, series_key, episode_number, category_id, body, ai_generated, qc_status, source_format, status, confidence_score, related_ayah_id, pdf_ebook_id, published_at)
SELECT 'Episode 6: Khalifah di Bumi dan Ahli Ibadah', 'kisah-dawud-06-khalifah-dan-ibadah', 'id', 'kisah-dawud', 6, 1, 'Puncak kisah Dawud adalah amanah yang Allah bebankan kepadanya sebagai pemimpin yang adil. Allah berfirman, "Wahai Dawud! Sesungguhnya Kami menjadikan engkau khalifah (penguasa) di bumi, maka berilah keputusan (perkara) di antara manusia dengan adil dan janganlah engkau mengikuti hawa nafsu, karena akan menyesatkan engkau dari jalan Allah…" (QS. Sad: 26).

Ayat ini menegaskan bahwa kekuasaan adalah amanah untuk menegakkan keadilan, bukan alat memenuhi hawa nafsu. Dawud menjalankan amanah itu, dan ilmunya kelak diwariskan kepada putranya. Allah berfirman, "Dan sungguh, Kami telah memberikan ilmu kepada Dawud dan Sulaiman… Dan Sulaiman telah mewarisi Dawud…" (QS. An-Naml: 15-16).

Di balik kedudukannya sebagai raja dan nabi, Dawud adalah ahli ibadah yang tekun. Allah menyebutnya "awwab" — yang banyak kembali kepada-Nya (QS. Sad: 17). Ketekunan ibadahnya menjadi teladan sepanjang masa, sehingga puasa dan salat malamnya dijadikan tolok ukur ibadah yang paling dicintai Allah.

Hikmah: Dawud memadukan keadilan seorang pemimpin dengan kerendahan hati seorang hamba. Ia kuat namun selalu kembali kepada Allah, berkuasa namun tetap beribadah — teladan penguasa yang tidak dilalaikan oleh kekuasaannya.

Sumber & Catatan: dalil dari Al-Qur''an — QS. Sad: 26, 17; An-Naml: 15-16. Keutamaan ibadah Dawud disebut dalam hadits sahih riwayat Bukhari & Muslim: "Puasa yang paling dicintai Allah adalah puasa Dawud; beliau berpuasa sehari dan berbuka sehari. Dan salat yang paling dicintai Allah adalah salat Dawud; beliau tidur separuh malam, salat sepertiganya, dan tidur seperenamnya" (HR. Bukhari no. 1131 & Muslim no. 1159).', 0, 'qc_pending', 'ai_original', 'published', 1.0,
  (SELECT id FROM ayah WHERE surah_id = 38 AND number = 26), NULL, datetime('now');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO stories (title, slug, lang, series_key, episode_number, category_id, body, ai_generated, qc_status, source_format, status, confidence_score, related_ayah_id, pdf_ebook_id, published_at)
SELECT 'Episode 6: Successor on Earth and a Devoted Worshipper', 'kisah-dawud-06-khalifah-dan-ibadah', 'en', 'kisah-dawud', 6, 1, 'The summit of Dawud''s story is the trust Allah placed on him as a just ruler. Allah said, "O David, indeed We have made you a successor upon the earth, so judge between the people in truth and do not follow [your own] desire, as it will lead you astray from the way of Allah…" (Qur''an 38:26).

This verse affirms that power is a trust for establishing justice, not a tool to serve desire. Dawud fulfilled that trust, and his knowledge was later inherited by his son. Allah said, "And We had certainly given to David and Solomon knowledge… And Solomon inherited David…" (Qur''an 27:15-16).

Behind his rank as king and prophet, Dawud was a diligent worshipper. Allah called him "awwab" — one who constantly turns back to Him (Qur''an 38:17). His devotion became a timeless model, so that his fasting and night prayer were made the measure of the worship most beloved to Allah.

Reflection: Dawud combined the justice of a ruler with the humility of a servant. He was strong yet always returning to Allah, powerful yet still worshipping — a model of a ruler undistracted by his own power.

Source & Note: evidence from the Qur''an — 38:26, 38:17; 27:15-16. The excellence of Dawud''s worship is stated in an authentic hadith reported by al-Bukhari & Muslim: "The most beloved fasting to Allah is the fasting of Dawud; he fasted a day and broke a day. And the most beloved prayer to Allah is the prayer of Dawud; he slept half the night, prayed a third of it, and slept a sixth of it" (Bukhari no. 1131 & Muslim no. 1159).', 0, 'qc_pending', 'ai_original', 'published', 1.0,
